<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,1055,1513]" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">
We think that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[343,548,1055,1081]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis box="[343,548,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">Cryptantha pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely a close relative of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[848,982,1055,1081]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis box="[848,982,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In general habit, the two species are quite similar. Aside from the 
<typeStatus box="[397,448,1091,1117]" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">type</typeStatus>
, all vouchers (if determined beyond genus) were originally identified as either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">Cryptantha maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[316,646,1127,1153]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maritima" variety="cedrosensis">
<emphasis box="[316,455,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[516,646,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">cedrosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[662,872,1127,1153]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis box="[662,872,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">Cryptantha pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1004,1143,1127,1153]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis box="[1004,1143,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having linear, pustulate bracts at the base of the cymules and scattered among the flowers. It is especially similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rebman &amp; M. G. Simpson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1171,1422,1163,1189]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maritima" variety="vizcainensis">
<emphasis box="[1171,1231,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. m.</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1287,1422,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">vizcainensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a solely strigose stem vestiture, is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[722,969,1199,1225]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maritima" variety="cedrosensis">
<emphasis box="[722,783,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. m.</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[839,969,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">cedrosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having four ovules and four nutlets that are heteromorphic (by size alone in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[551,658,1235,1261]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis box="[551,658,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with the odd nutlet axial (nearest the inflorescence axis, as opposed to away from it), and is similar to both varieties in having relatively large corollas. It differs from all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1314,1452,1271,1297]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis box="[1314,1452,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
varieties in lacking “rough” (minutely tuberculate) nutlets, but we note that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1007,1145,1307,1333]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis box="[1007,1145,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens will sometimes have a single nutlet; when so, it is smooth. In addition, the similar geographic range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[1108,1314,1343,1369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis box="[1108,1314,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">Cryptantha pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1329,1396,1343,1369]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[136,229,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,194,919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[152,1436,190,926]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. A,B. Cryptantha pondii, distribution map of three known collections. Georeference point for the type, Pond 22, approximate; that of Gentry 8684 placed as a centroid of three different georeferenced estimates. Maps from ©Google 2020, INEGI Data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426150" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426150/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rebman &amp; M. G. Simpson" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,459,1379,1405]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maritima" variety="vizcainensis">
<emphasis box="[136,271,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[324,459,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">vizcainensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[474,540,1379,1405]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1885,1907]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,217,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[219,1369,190,1861]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution maps of varieties of Cryptantha maritima. Data from Baja Flora (2021), CCH2 (2021), GBIF (2020), and SEINet (2021), all specimens annotated by the authors (Appendix 1). A, B. Distribution in North America. A. Full distribution map. B. Close-up of Vizcaíno Peninsula and adjacent islands. Note location of type populations and restriction of C. maritima var. cedrosensis to Cedros Island and of C. maritima var. vizcainensis to the western Vizcaíno region. Black dots=C. maritima var. maritima; red dots=C. maritima var. pilosa; green triangles= C. maritima var. cedrosensis; yellow squares= C. maritima var. vizcainensis. C. Distribution of C. maritima var. pilosa in Argentina, South America, data from GBIF (2020).All maps from ©Google 2021, INEGI Data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426140/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) may be indicative of a common evolutionary origin. We considered, but rejected, the taxonomic treatment of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[449,554,1415,1441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis box="[449,554,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[730,867,1415,1441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="13" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis box="[730,867,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="198">C. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because we have no clear evidence of relationships between the two species. Future molecular phylogenetic studies should clarify the interrelationships among these taxa.
</paragraph>
